“谢谢你的勇敢”，是鲜花上出现得最多的悼词。
"Thank you for your bravery," is the most popular eulogy on flowers.
本文首发于南方周末 未经授权 不得转载文 |南方周末记者 李在磊 黎央责任编辑 |张玥Play▲（黎央/视频）2月7日，是武汉市中心医院李文亮医生离世的第一天。
This article began at Southern Weekend and was not allowed to reproduce without authorization. Li Jie, Li's duty editor at Li Li, the Southern Weekend reporter, was the first day of Dr. Li Wenliang's death on February 7, the day of his death at Wuhan Central Hospital.
人们的悼念，在医院门诊大楼的大门口也持续了一整天。
The tributes also continued throughout the day at the entrance to the hospital clinic building.
晚九时许，医院门口的悼念者吹起了口哨，尖利的哨音划过黑夜。
Around nine o'clock in the evening, mourners whistled in front of the hospital, whistling sharply across the night.
在武汉市区，许多市民自发发起了悼念李文亮的活动，人们点亮灯光，有人吹哨，有人高喊“武汉加油。
In Wuhan city, many citizens spontaneously launched a memorial to Li Wenliang activities, people lit lights, some whistles, someone shouted "Wuhan refueling.
”（李在磊/图）2月7日白天，网传李文亮医生的妻子发出求救贴，她目前位于湖北省枣阳市的娘家，家中老人染病、大人受苦。
During the day, Feb. 7, the wife of Dr. Li Wenliang, now at her mother's home in Zaoyang, Hubei province, suffered from illness and adult suffering.
南方周末记者联系了求救贴公布的电话，确认发布信息的不是她本人，而是亲属，此后这个号码则无法联系。
Southern Weekend reporter contacted a phone call posted by SOS, confirming that it was not she but relatives who released the information and that the number could not be contacted thereafter.
南方周末记者赶赴枣阳市，但此前被称作唯一不封城的襄阳，高速公路已经封路，无法通行，其下辖的枣阳市部署了最严格的封城令，不许陌生人进出。
Southern Weekend reporters rushed to Zaoyang City, but previously known as the only open city Xiangyang, the highway has closed, impassable, under the jurisdiction of the city of Zaoyang deployed the strictest order, no stranger access.
南方周末记者只得在距离枣阳30公里外的小路折返。
Southern Weekend reporter had to in Zaoyang 30 kilometers away from the path back.
晚21时，南方周末记者在武汉市中心医院门诊大楼门前，看到仍有市民来献花。
At 21 p. m., Southern Weekend reporter in front of the outpatient building of Wuhan Central Hospital, saw that there are still citizens to offer flowers.
医院门口摆着三幅李文亮戴着口罩的黑白照片，黄色、白色的菊花，簇拥着照片中的面庞，四周点缀着星星点点的灯。
In front of the hospital were three black-and-white photographs of Li Wenhuang wearing a mask, yellow and white chrysanthemums surrounded by a picture of the face, dotted with tiny lights.
（李在磊/图）一位大哥鞠完躬，抑制不住悲伤，自己躲在角落里，扶着栏杆啜泣。
(Li in Lei / Picture) A big brother bowed and couldn't help feeling sad. He hid himself in a corner and sobbed against the railing.
他在鲜花的贴纸上写道：“李文亮医生，谢谢你的勇敢！”“谢谢你的勇敢”，是鲜花上出现得最多的悼词。
"Thank you for your courage, Dr. Li Wenliang," he wrote on the flower sticker. "Thank you for your courage." It was the most popular eulogy on flowers.
除此之外，武汉市民还对这位刚刚离去的医生说：“英雄，一路走好”、“李文亮，谢谢你来过”、“公民李文亮”以及“李文亮医生，谢谢你所做的一切！”（李在磊/图）（黎央/图）（李在磊/图）（黎央/图）Play▲（李在磊/视频）附近木技花艺馆的老板说，“封城”没多久，他们便关门歇业。
Besides, Wuhan city residents said to the recently departed doctor, "Hero, all the way, thank you for coming," "Citizen Li Wenliang" and "Thank you, Dr. Li Wenliang!" (Li Wenliang) (Li Jilai / Tu) (Li Jilai / Tu) Li Wenliang (Li Jilai / Tu).
就在今天，打电话订购鲜花的人特别多，想要给李文亮买束鲜花。
Just today, more people phoned to order flowers and wanted to buy a bunch of flowers for him.
他一趟又一趟地往返于花店与医院之间。
He commutes from florist to hospital.
（李在磊/图）（李在磊/图）（李在磊/图）（李在磊/图）征集《南方周末》现向所有身处新冠肺炎一线的读者公开征集新闻线索。
Li Jilei / Picture Li Jilai / Li Jilei / Picture Li Jilai / Li Jilai / Picture Li Jilei / Picture Li collecting Southern Weekend is now soliciting news leads from all the readers who are on the front line of the new crown pneumonia.
我们欢迎武汉及周边城市医患联系记者，提供防疫前线的一手资讯，讲述您的新春疫情见闻。
We welcome Wuhan and surrounding city doctors and patients contact reporters, provide a first-hand epidemic prevention information, to tell you about the New Year.
若您不在武汉，但您身处之所也有与疫情相关的重要新闻线索，亦欢迎您与我们分享。
If you are not in Wuhan, but you are in a place where you also have important news clues related to the epidemic, you are welcome to share with us.
疫情仍在蔓延，南方周末将执笔记录每位国人在疫情面前的希望与困境，与广大读者共同面对疫情。
The epidemic is still spreading. Southern Weekend will write about the hopes and difficulties of every Chinese people in the face of the epidemic and face the epidemic together with readers.
祝愿所有读者朋友们，新春平安。
Wish all readers a safe New Year.
